 "name": "Appendix B2 — Reliability Drill (retry + fail-closed)",
 "nodes": [
  {
   "parameters": {
    "content": "📖 [Course documentation](https://ezponda.github.io/ai-agents-course/appendix_b2_production_reliability.html)\n## Reliability drill — Retry + Timeout + fail-closed\n**Goal:** See the node-level reliability settings in one place. The HTTP node **retries** on failure with a delay, gives up after a **timeout**, and on final failure routes to the **error output** so you can **fail closed** (stop) instead of pretending it worked.\n\n### Where the settings live\nOpen **Call an API → Settings**: *Retry On Fail*, *Max Tries*, *Wait Between Tries*, and *On Error* (Stop / Continue / Continue (error output)). *Timeout* is in the node's **Options**.\n\n⚠️ Retries suit **transient** errors (429/500/timeout). Do **not** auto-retry validation or permission errors — fix the request instead.",
    "height": 360,
    "width": 640
   },
   "id": "23000000-0000-4000-8000-0000000000s1",
   "name": "NOTE",
   "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
